  <front>
   <head>By a Person of Quality.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">from Strife, from urban Throngs, and Noise.</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Here dwells my Soul amidst domestic Joys:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No ratling Coaches serious Thoughts annoy;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor busy prating Fools my Peace destroy:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Wrapt up in all the Sweets of rural Ease,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">My great Creator's Works my Senses please.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Mind, in peaceful Solitude, has Room</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To range in Thought, and ramble far from home,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Others may court the Joys which Princes give,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Whilst I, in sacred Silence, truly live.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
